# Marketing Analytics

Guidelines for measurement, attribution, experimentation, and data-driven marketing decisions.

## Key Metrics by Function

| Function | Primary Metrics | Secondary Metrics |
|----------|----------------|-------------------|
| Demand Gen | Pipeline generated, MQLs, SQLs | CPL, conversion rates, velocity |
| Content | Organic traffic, engaged sessions | Rankings, backlinks, content-to-lead |
| Paid Media | ROAS, CPA, pipeline from paid | CTR, quality score, impression share |
| Email | Revenue per email, conversion rate | Open rate, click rate, unsubscribe |
| Brand | Aided awareness, NPS, SOV | Branded search volume, sentiment |
| Growth | Activation rate, retention, LTV | K-factor, time to value, expansion |

## Attribution Model Selection

| Scenario | Recommended Model |
|----------|------------------|
| Short sales cycle (< 7 days) | Last touch or first touch |
| Medium cycle (1-3 months) | U-shaped or linear |
| Long cycle (3+ months, enterprise) | W-shaped or data-driven |
| Brand-heavy strategy | First touch weighted |
| Multi-channel, high volume | Data-driven / algorithmic |

## Attribution Implementation Essentials

- UTM parameter standards across all channels
- CRM source/campaign fields mapping leads to campaigns
- Touchpoint tracking for every meaningful interaction
- Data warehouse joins unifying ad platform, CRM, and product data

